==English==

===Etymology===
Confer {{F.}} ''[[naturalisme]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A state of nature; [[conform]]ity to [[nature]].
# ''Metaphaphoric:'' The doctrine of those who deny a supernatural agency in the miracles and revelations recorded in the Bible, and in spiritual influences; also, any system of philosophy which refers the phenomena of nature to a blind force or forces acting necessarily or according to fixed laws, excluding origination or direction by one intelligent will.

